# Task #135: the (RomM)-twin duplicates mean the head can reference one twin while the
# card (after cleanup / re-mirror) holds the other. Same rom_id, same game: resume the
# surviving twin instead of the empty state. C2 retires the duplicates; Continue must be
# robust to the drift regardless.
desc Continue dispatcher: head names the (RomM) twin, card has the clean twin -> twin fallback launches
invoke ctpak
config paired
sdfile+ Roms/Game Boy Advance (GBA)/✓ Emerald.gba
sdtext .userdata/shared/Lodor/continue-head.txt	/Roms/Game Boy Advance (GBA)/✓ Emerald (RomM).gba\tEmerald\n
engine 0|
engine 0|RESULT pushed=1 staged=0
engine 0|RESULT reconciled=1
expect_exit 0
expect_trace PRES timeout=-1 msg='Continuing Emerald...'
expect_trace EMULAUNCH rom=
expect_trace ✓ Emerald.gba'
expect_log continue: entry 1 resolved via=twin
